==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gingerly
<hw>Gin"ger*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E. <ets>ginger</ets>
brittle, tender; cf. dial. Sw. <ets>gingla</ets>, <ets>g⟦aum⟧ngla</ets>,
to go gently, totter, akin to E. <ets>gang</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Cautiously; timidly; fastidiously; daintily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What is't that you took up so <qex>gingerly</qex> ?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gingerness</ent>⟦br⟧
